The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Hanif: Sachin is a jewel
                                                                                                                       7                                      Hanif: Sachin is a jewel
                      
	Karachi: Former Pakistan captain Hanif Mohammed has termed Sachin Tendulkar as the cricketing jewel of subcontinent and said the 36-year-old right-hander is destined to break many more records in the coming years.         
	According to the legendary wicketkeeper-batsman, Indias Lala Amarnath and Sachin Tendulkar, West Indian Sir Garry Sobers and Brian Lara are the best batsmen of the last century.         
	His (Tendulkars) hunger and passion as a batsman and for the game is amazing. I still make it a point to sit down and watch him batting... He is a cricketing jewel of the subcontinent, he said.         
	Habib also rated India as his favourite opponent.         
	Playing against India was always a challenge in my career and some of my best innings came against them, Hanif said, on the occasion of his 75th birthday Monday.         
	Hanif played 55 Tests and 238 first class matches in a glittering career, earned the sobriquet of Little Master for the longest innings in Test history  970-minute 337 against the West Indies in Bridgetown in 1957-58.         
	Delighted to be a part of Pakistans cricketing history he said: It has been a wonderful career and great life. I am thankful to almighty Allah for celebrating my 75th birthday.(PTI)                                                                                                                     
